'''Bruna Beatriz Benites Soares''', or simply '''Bruna''', (born October 16, 1985) is a [[Brazil]]ian [[Association football|footballer]]. She plays as a [[Defender (association football)|defender]] for [[S<U+00E3>o Jos<U+00E9> Esporte Clube (women)|S<U+00E3>o Jos<U+00E9>]] and the [[Brazil women's national football team]].

==Personal life==
She is a member of [[The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints]].<ref>http://www.deseretnews.com/top/845/0/Mormon-athletes-competing-in-the-2012-Summer-Olympics-in-London.html#/top/845/19/Bruna-Beatriz-Benites-Soares-Mormon-athletes-competing-in-the-2012-Summer-Olympics-in-London.html</ref> She is also has a degree in Physiotherapy having studied at Universidade Catolica Dom Bosco in [[Campo Grande]].<ref>http://www.london2012.com/athlete/bruna-1094481/</ref>

==National Team==
Bruna made her debut at the 2012 Summer Olympics. She received a [[Penalty card#Yellow_card|yellow card]] against Great Britain and in the Quarter Final defeat to Japan.<ref>http://www.fifa.com/worldfootball/statisticsandrecords/players/player=356754/index.html</ref>

